---

<dialog id="info-dialog" class="info-dialog" closedby="any">
  <form method="dialog">
    <header>
      <h2>Design Squiggle</h2>
      <button class="close-dialog" aria-label="Close dialog">
        <svg
          width="24"
          height="24"
          fill="none"
          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
          stroke-width="1.5"
          stroke="currentColor"
        >
          <path
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            d="M6 18 18 6M6 6l12 12"></path>
        </svg>
      </button>
    </header>
    <p>
      The Design Squiggle is one of the clearest representations of how real
      product work happens. It shows that every worthwhile outcome begins in
      uncertainty, where ideas are loose, information is incomplete, and the
      path forward is rarely obvious. Through exploration, testing, and repeated
      refinement, that messy beginning gradually becomes a clear and effective
      solution. A charming insult to anyone who believes good products arrive
      fully formed.
    </p>
    <p>
      That idea reflects how I work as a product designer. I do not expect
      clarity at the start. My role is to create it. I move through ambiguity by
      understanding users, questioning assumptions, shaping systems, and
      refining ideas until they become something people can actually use. The
      early mess is not something to avoid. It is where the real work begins.
    </p>
    <p>
      It also reflects how I work as a product manager. Knowing how to code
      helps me understand the work being delegated, make better decisions, and
      collaborate more effectively with engineers. It gives me a clearer sense
      of effort, constraints, and trade-offs without needing to control every
      implementation detail like some doomed tyrant. AI adds another layer of
      leverage by helping me research faster, explore ideas more broadly, and
      move from concept to execution with greater speed while keeping judgment
      at the center.
    </p>
  </form>
</dialog>
<style>
  .info-dialog {
    margin: 0 0 0 auto;
    inset-block: 0;
    max-width: 60ch;
    height: 100%;
    max-height: 100%;
    overflow-y: auto;
    border: none;
    transition:
      opacity 300ms ease-in-out,
      transform 300ms ease-in-out,
      display 300ms allow-discrete;
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateX(10%);
    &::backdrop {
      background-image: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, #0000008b);
      opacity: 0;
      transition: inherit;
    }
    &:open,
    &[open] {
      pointer-events: all;
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateX(0%);
      &::backdrop {
        opacity: 1;
      }
      @starting-style {
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateX(10%);
        &::backdrop {
          opacity: 0;
        }
      }
    }
    & > form {
      display: grid;
      row-gap: 1em;
      padding: var(--py);
      & > header {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        align-items: flex-start;
        & > h2 {
          font-size: 1.25em;
        }
        & > button {
          & > svg {
            vertical-align: top;
            width: 1.5em;
            height: 1.5em;
          }
        }
      }
      & > p {
        letter-spacing: 0.015em;
        color: #ffffffd6;
        line-height: 1.5;
      }
    }
  }
</style>
